<p>The Dr. Phillips and Windermere areas showcase larger luxury homes averaging 2,500+ square feet, making them ideal candidates for 8-10kW solar systems paired with high-efficiency multi-zone HVAC systems. Newer developments like Lake Nona and Horizon West often include energy-efficient construction and HOAs that support solar installations, with optimal roof orientations for maximum solar production. East Orlando neighborhoods including Avalon Park and Waterford Lakes feature newer construction with adequate electrical panels for solar integration and modern HVAC infrastructure.</p>

